# Action security

- Never log, print, or embed `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `MCP_KEY`, `MCP_URL`, or action
  inputs that carry secrets into prompts, fixtures, step summaries, or commits.
- Claude must remain MCP-scoped: allowed tools are ProductNow MCP only; the
  injected git diff is its only code view.
- Do not add steps that write commits, open PRs, or push to the consumer repo.
- Workflows in this repo must use `permissions: contents: read` unless a job
  truly needs more, and every `uses:` must be pinned to a full 40-character SHA.
- Consumer guidance should recommend pinning this action by commit SHA.
